---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Affiliate disclosure"
  description="How BES3 handles commercial links and sponsored content."
>
  <section class="page-hero shell">
    <div><p class="eyebrow">TRANSPARENCY</p><h1>Our links, explained.</h1></div><p class="lede">
      BES3 may earn a commission when a reader buys through selected links. The price does not
      change for the reader.
    </p>
  </section>
  <section class="section reading-width article-body">
    <h2>Affiliate links</h2><p>
      Affiliate links are tagged beside the first relevant button or link in an article. They are
      chosen because the destination is useful for the reader, not because it guarantees a
      commission.
    </p>
    <h2>Sponsored work</h2><p>
      Paid editorial assignments are labelled Sponsored. Payment does not buy an editorial
      conclusion. We do not publish a sponsored article without a written scope and an editorial
      boundary.
    </p>
    <h2>Official destinations</h2><p>
      Where possible, buttons identify the merchant destination and use the official site. We do not
      use hidden redirects, coupon interception, fake scarcity or unapproved creative.
    </p>
    <h2>Questions</h2><p>
      For questions about a commercial relationship, write to <a href="mailto:editorial@bes3.com"
        >editorial@bes3.com</a
      >.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
